 out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Filiol was born in 1220 as the son of Filiol. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Lucy Filiol."},"et":{"1220–":"1220–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1250":"1250"},"fi":{"1220–":"1220–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1250":"1250"},"fr":{"1220–":"1220–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","lifeSummary":"Hugh Filiol est né en 1220, fils de Filiol. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. Lucy Filiol."},"de":{"1220–":"1220–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1190–Male":"1190–Verstorben","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","lifeSummary":"Hugh Filiol wurde 1220, als Sohn von Filiol geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs. Lucy Filiol mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1220–":"1220–Desede","1220–Male":"1220–Desede","–Female":"Desede","1250–Male":"1250–Desede","1190–Male":"1190–Desede","1190":"1190","1220":"1220","1250":"1250"},"hu":{"1220–":"1220–elhunyt","1220–Male":"1220–elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1250–Male":"1250–elhunyt","1190–Male":"1190–elhunyt","1190":